        "orario": "23:47 - 5 Marzo",
        "timestamp": 1772750859,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Trump urges Iranian diplomats around the world to request asylum Middle East Issued on: 05/03/2026 - 23:47 Share Trump touted the U.S. ​military actions in Iran on Thursday, saying they were ‌destroying Tehran's missile and drone capability and that \"their navy is gone - 24 ships in three days,\" as ‌he called on Iranian diplomats to request asylum and help shape ​a better country. \"We also urge Iranian diplomats around the world to request asylum and to help us shape a ​new and better Iran,\" he said. FRANCE 24's Fraser Jackson reports from Washington. Video by: Fraser JACKSON Keywords for this article Iran diplomacy Donald Trump Israel strikes Beirut’s southern suburbs after issuing a blanket evacuation order 05/03/2026 Middle East Seafarers can refuse to sail through Mideast Gulf region, main union says 05/03/2026 Middle East Israeli army announces start of airstrikes on southern Beirut suburb 05/03/2026 Middle East Trump unlikely to ever commit ground US forces to Iran, expert says 05/03/2026 Middle East US claims Iran's missile capabilities 'severely degraded' 05/03/2026 Middle East Qatar says 14 ballistic missiles and 4 drones intercepted 05/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran has no Plan B, warns Scott Lucas: 'Trump just wants to kill people and blow stuff up' 05/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon: Tens of thousands of residents displaced ahead of fresh Israeli strikes 05/03/2026 Middle East Israel's Lebanon offensive 'may ultimately legitimise Hezbollah, reinforce narrative of resistance' 05/03/2026 Middle East"
